cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CE, cs.CR

The paper discusses the role of human decision-making in the adoption of smart grid technologies, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The focus on consumer behavior and decision-making suggests a connection to the subfield of cyberpsychology (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the potential benefits of incorporating renewable energy and energy storage units, which relates to the subfield of sustainable computing (cs.SI) and the use of optimization techniques (cs.CE) to improve the operation of the smart grid.
